[[wowAnalytics=wowAnalytics();"Port In Volume Info:
In the last two weeks (between [[formatDateTime(previousWeek_startDate,'MMMM dd, yyyy')]] - [[latestWeek_endDate]]) with [[wowAnalytics.highest_portInNetwork]], Vodafone has seen the most number of connections ported in compared to the previous week. The port in connections  from [[wowAnalytics.highest_portInNetwork]] increased by about [[wowAnalytics.highest_portInNumbers]] numbers in the lastest week. The network with least port in count is [[wowAnalytics.least_portInNetwork]] with about [[abs(wowAnalytics.least_portInNumbers)]] [[getDirection(wowAnalytics.least_portInNumbers,'more','less')]] than the previous week.

Port Out Volume Info:
Vodafone has lost about [[abs(wowAnalytics.highest_portOutNumbers)]] connections to  [[wowAnalytics.highest_portOutNetwork]] network in the current week compared to the previous week. In the current week , Vodafone has seen about [[wowAnalytics.highest_portOutCurrentCount]] numbers ported to [[wowAnalytics.highest_portOutNetwork]] in the current week alone, which was [[wowAnalytics.highest_portOutPrevCount]] in the last week.

NetVolume Info:
The most profitable network that has seen more connections ported in than ported out connections is [[wowAnalytics.highest_netVolumeNetork]]. It has seen net volume increase by about [[wowAnalytics.highest_netVolumneCount]] in the latest week compared to the previous week. The total number of connections ported in from [[wowAnalytics.highest_netVolumeNetork]] in the current week is [[wowAnalytics.netVolumeNetwork_portInCount]] and about [[wowAnalytics.netVolume_portOutCount]] connection ported to it"]]

Also, Vodafone has lost about [[sixWeekAnalytics.portOutCount]] connections to other networks. The major loss of about [[sixWeekAnalytics.portOutCount_lostNumber]] connections is to the [[sixWeekAnalytics.portOutCount_network]] network.
